      "part_type": "Hadith",
      "path": "/books/al-kafi:7:4:1:9",
      "relations": null,
      "text": [
        " رَجُلٍ قَتَلَ رَجُلًا مُؤْمِناً قَالَ يُقَالُ لَهُ مُتْ أَيَّ مِيتَةٍ شِئْتَ إِنْ شِئْتَ يَهُودِيّاً وَ إِنْ شِئْتَ نَصْرَانِيّاً وَ إِنْ شِئْتَ مَجُوسِيّاً ."
      ],
      "translations": {
        "en.hubeali": [
          "Ali, from his father, from Ibn Abu Umeyr, from Saeed Al Arzaq, ",
          "(It has been narrated) from Abu Abdullah<sup>asws</sup> regarding a man who killed a Believing man. He<sup>asws</sup> said: ‘It would be said to him: ‘Die whichever death you like – if you so like, as a Jew, and if you so like, as a Christian, and if you so like, as a Magian!’."
        ]
      }
    }
